Riding on the potential of the African Continental Free Trade Agreement (AfCFTA) goal of promoting inter-African trade, NSIA Insurance said it is determined to drive insurance acceptance across the twelve African countries where it exists. NSIA Insurance  The organisation said subsidiaries within NSIA Group would combine their distinct talents to propel the insurance business and foster relationships between employees and management while improving work conditions. The Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer of the firm, Ebelechukwu Nwachukwu, said: “’Project Act Together is a great initiative that will improve working relationships and promote cohesion among NSIA subsidiaries in Africa. NSIA Nigeria will continue to instil the 12 common goals and connect its culture with the Group.” According to her, the project began with a message from the Group President, Jean Kacou Diagou, on January 4, 2022. NSIA subsidiaries across Africa tuned in to listen to the message and learn about the 2021 accomplishments as well as 2022 goals. 